<Base title="About INNO Transformer Temperature Products" description="Learn how INNO presents focused transformer oil and winding temperature indicator selection, technical data and direct email support for global projects."><section class="page-hero"><div class="container"><p class="eyebrow">About INNO</p><h1>Focused on Transformer Temperature Instruments</h1><p>INNO supports product selection for oil-immersed transformer oil temperature indicators, winding temperature indicators and integrated monitoring devices.</p></div></section><section class="section"><article class="container prose"><h2>A narrow product boundary</h2><p>This website concentrates on instruments used to indicate, control and remotely monitor thermal conditions on oil-immersed transformers. The product range includes OTI gauges for top-oil temperature, WTI gauges for simulated winding temperature and a powered device for oil temperature, oil level and pressure.</p><p>A focused product boundary improves technical communication. It prevents a top-oil thermometer from being presented as direct winding hot-spot measurement and prevents a powered monitoring device from being treated as interchangeable with a self-contained mechanical indicator.</p><h2>Selection before promotion</h2><p>Transformer instruments are model-driven products. A family name may cover several switch quantities, signal outputs, supplies, scales, capillary lengths and environmental suffixes. INNO asks for the complete requirement before a configuration is treated as final.</p><p>Product pages organize planning values for efficient model selection and state where final confirmation is required. The applicable datasheet, drawing and terminal diagram remain the controlling documents for an order.</p><h2>Support for global projects</h2><p>The website is written for transformer manufacturers, utilities, EPC contractors, panel builders, distributors and maintenance teams worldwide. Contact is handled directly by email so drawings, nameplate photographs and project specifications can stay with the technical discussion.</p><p>INNO does not use a website form on this site. Send the application and model data to <a href="mailto:fjinnonet@gmail.com">fjinnonet@gmail.com</a> to request a selection review, current datasheet or commercial quotation.</p></article></section><EmailCTA subject="About INNO transformer temperature products" /></Base>
